description:
My place is good for couples, solo adventurers, business travelers, and families (with kids). Come way uptown to beautiful, historic Washington Heights and experience a new side of New York. It's easy to explore NYC as you're walking distance from the 1, A, and C trains. My apartment is kid-friendly, not kid-centric so adults traveling without kids will be just as comfortable as families. This quiet building is a relaxing respite after a long NYC day or night!

There are so many places that people can sleep comfortably. Kids will love it and parents will love having space(s) away from them! Party people can use it as a crash pad; Uber and other cabs happily come here. Late night the 1 train runs very slowly, so keep that in mind.

Make yourself at home! I've provided snack baskets with treats for you and there's room in the fridge for some items. You can use the stove, oven, cookware, and appliances, but please don't eat anything that's in my freezer or pantry!

In most cases, I'll be staying right upstairs in another apartment with my child and we are home starting from 7:00 PM. Anything you need, I'll be happy to assist you, even come down and take care of it for you personally. Other than that, I won't be bothering you and you can make yourself at home! If I'll be out of town, feel free to text me and I'll get back to you immediately.

This is a gorgeous neighborhood that is getting a lot of love and upgrades from new incoming residents. However, it still has its ethnic charms and you should really support and patronize the local businesses on Broadway that make this area unique and special. Riverbank State Park is 10 blocks downtown and if your kids can handle walking and weather permits, you can actually walk across 155th to Yankee Stadium.

I recommend Kennedy Car Service if you want door-to-door service 
Tell cabs you want to go to 156th Street and Riverside 
Unless you're in a rush, I don't recommend transferring to the 2/3 to get to Times Square. Just stay on it until 42nd St. If you do decide to transfer, do so at 96th St.
If you drive, PLEASE PLEASE PLEASE note the alternate side parking rules so you don't get a ticket. Call me when you park and read the sign to me if necessary. NYC parking is not a game.

The outer elevator door doesn't open automatically when it reaches your floor. You have to open it yourself.
There's a laundry and trash room downstair in the lobby near the mailboxes.
I'll leave the laundry card for you to add money to, the machine only accepts denominations of $5 bills or higher. No coins or dollar bills or credit cards.

photos.caption: Living Room with a large window that gets plenty of sunlight. Lay out on the couch and take a nap after a long day of sight-seeing (or alternatively, fall out onto the couch after a long night of partying)
Sleeper sofa that sleeps one comfortable. Perfect for a teen or tween who stays up later than younger kids in the other room

TV has Roku; connect to Netflix*, Hulu*, Amazon Instant Video or use the antenna to watch regular network TV. No cable, but who needs it? You're in New York City! 
*Shared, may not always be available, but feel free to use your own accounts
Kids' room with lots of books and toys to keep kids occupied when you're wiped out from a long NYC day!
Two sleepy little travelers/sightseers will be very happy to climb into these comfy bunk beds at night. High-quality mattresses are comfortable even for an adult.

Kids feeling a little homesick? Open up the full-size sleeper sofa and spend the night in their room. You'll awaken with no stiff back or neck thanks to the comfy mattress cover. (An older child can sleep in here, too)
Nice snack/activity table where kids can eat or draw.
Extremely comfortable queen-sized bed in a separate room so you can relax in peace after a long day of shopping and sightseeing or a long night of partying
Look, just LOOK, at this gorgeous building!
